04/02/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Vladimir Lazarevic, one of four Serbian army and police generals indicted by the UN war crimes tribunal, arrived in The Hague on Thursday (3 February). Serbian Justice Minister Zoran Stojkovic and Zoran Loncar of the National Council for Hague Tribunal Co-operation accompanied the general, who surrendered to authorities last week. Lazarevic is facing charges related to his role during the 1999 Kosovo conflict. His initial appearance before the tribunal is expected next week. (B92, Tanjug, AP, Reuters, AFP, BBC - 03/02/05)
